    "narrative": "The offensive ceiling for the Austin Waves today is anchored by **Jackson Merrill** (66.12) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (61.04), both of whom clear the 60-point \"Strong\" threshold despite facing challenging right-handed starters. **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a robust platoon advantage against Luis Castillo, pushing his efficiency score upward through favorable batting order placement. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** maintains a high floor due to his elite xwOBA metrics, mitigating the impact of facing a tough arm like Sproat. While **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (59.95) just missed the 60-point tier, he remains an essential start, utilizing his dynamic platoon advantage against Ashcraft to provide a high-floor contribution that keeps the offense balanced.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Brady House**, who posted a 47.22, narrowly failing to displace the lower-scoring but higher-ceiling options in our active roster. While **Brady House** has the utility profile to rotate in, he was ultimately sidelined because his projected efficiency against Ashcraft was diluted by the pitcher's tendency to hold runners, significantly capping the SB potential we prioritize for our 5x5 build. Meanwhile, we must proceed with caution regarding **Gunnar Henderson** (47.79); his score is depressed by a difficult matchup against Messick and an unfavorable platoon split, exacerbated by a 36% rain risk in the forecast. Should the weather deteriorate, we will need to monitor the bench closely, though internal options like **Coby Mayo**\u2014who also faces Messick\u2014offer little relief given his own sub-44 projection today.",
